library(SiteSelectR)
library(SiteSelectR)
The SiteSelectR library works with the terra and sf  libraries. Both are used in SiteSelectR to handle raster data (terra) and vectorized shapefile data (sf).
We walk through visualizing our chosen cells, and choosing more below. However, these functions are wrapped into our site_select() function which takes a latitude and longitude value of the users' first site, the number of desired sites, and the raster stack data. We provide functions to prepare raster data for site_select() and create a sampling extent to choose sites - two necessary steps for running site_select() which is the main function in SiteSelectR.
